President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing Small Business Week and praising the role of small businesses in the American economy. According to the proclamation, small businesses employ nearly 58 million Americans and create two-thirds of net new, private-sector jobs in the United States. Trump highlights his administration's efforts to support small businesses, including tax cuts and reducing burdensome regulations. He also emphasizes the importance of fair trade deals, cybersecurity, education, skills training, and infrastructure investment in promoting small business growth. The proclamation calls on all Americans to acknowledge the contributions of entrepreneurs and small business owners to the nation's economy.